      • dataAlreadyConverted

        public static Boolean dataAlreadyConverted(Class parameterType,
                           List<Map<String,Object>> convertFrom,
                           String paramName)
        Is the data already converted by the user while loading the data. This can happen when a user has its own custom loader and converts the data while loading it. This may not be advisable as it brings in extra coupling but is still possible as sometimes it may be very simple to convert the data while loading it.
        Parameters:
        parameterType - the type of the input parameter
        convertFrom - the data to convert from
        paramName - the name of the parameter
        Returns:
        whether the data is already converted by the user while loading the data
